 {"id":"franken_numpy-ymu5","title":"numpy.fft: rfft python wrapper parity","description":"Add fnp_python.rfft passthrough wrapper around numpy.fft.rfft(a, n=None, axis=-1, norm=None, out=None). Returns a complex array of length n//2+1 from a real input. Include oracle test covering: default transform of real 1-D array, explicit n (zero-pad and truncate), explicit axis on 2-D input, norm='ortho'/'forward', and verify output dtype is complex.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T05:53:58.375920639Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T06:37:18.704868905Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T06:37:18.701312261Z","close_reason":"Already shipped: native-Rust rfft wrapper at crates/fnp-python/src/lib.rs:5171 with signature (a, n=None, norm=None) using the fnp-ufunc rfft backend and a corresponding test at line ~13655 covering default/backward/ortho/forward/bad-norm. My attempt to add a passthrough duplicate was reverted.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_numpy-yppw","title":"Match NumPy signal empty-input errors","description":"NumPy raises ValueError for empty np.convolve/np.correlate operands: np.convolve([], [1,2,3]) -> 'a cannot be empty', np.convolve([1,2,3], []) -> 'v cannot be empty', np.correlate([], [1,2,3]) -> 'first array argument cannot be empty', and np.correlate([1,2,3], []) -> 'second array argument cannot be empty'. Current signal_adversarial_cases.json expects empty_output for convolve_empty_a, convolve_empty_b, and correlate_empty_input. Update fnp-ufunc behavior and conformance fixtures/harness so empty signal operands fail with NumPy-compatible errors instead of returning empty arrays.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-18T13:10:41.606184519Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-18T13:24:44.465627623Z","closed_at":"2026-04-18T13:24:44.462658194Z","close_reason":"Matched NumPy convolve/correlate empty-operand errors and froze signal adversarial expected-error fixtures.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["conformance","parity","signal"]}
